From ba7303ad6af25a7f8f8a0a9354a3ea9a69286098 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Deng, Bing" <bing.deng@intel.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Jul 2026 15:59:09 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Port to ROS2 and bring up Mid-360/D415 on A2W

1. Migrate the codebase and launch files from ROS1 to ROS2, converting
   XML launch files to Python and updating package.xml and various
   source files for the new API.
2. Add configuration for the Mid-360 LiDAR and RealSense D415 camera
   on the A2W robot, including calibrated IMU/camera extrinsics.
3. Add per-frame LIO/VIO timing CSV export (wall-clock breakdown of
   receive, algorithm start, pose publish and map update stages) to
   support the E1 OFAT experiment, along with matching 1080p and
   LIO-only configs; gate it behind a new CMake option,
   ENABLE_PERFRAME_TIMING, disabled by default since the
   fopen/fprintf-per-frame instrumentation is unwanted overhead in
   production builds, and enable it explicitly for latency
   experiments with -DENABLE_PERFRAME_TIMING=ON.
4. Fix a DDS discovery race that could crash the node on startup by
   declaring camera parameters in the constructor and passing them
   explicitly to the NTU and Mid-360/D415 launch files instead of
   relying solely on parameter_blackboard.
5. Fix the inverted Mid-360 mount orientation on A2W.
6. Throttle the D415 image topic to 10 Hz across the A2W configs to
   cut CPU load without dropping below the required update rate, and
   refresh the README and NTU rviz config for the new setup.

Signed-off-by: Deng, Bing <bing.deng@intel.com>
